values.name: Conversation
values.description: A project to build natural language into apps, bots, and IoT devices.

values.name: Orchestration
values.description: A project to connect and orchestrate Conversation, Custom question answering and LUIS projects together in one single project.

values.name: CustomConversationSummarization
values.description: A project to build conversation summarization models which are able to summarize long conversations.

values.name: Conversation
values.description: Specifies the format for a conversational project.

values.name: Luis
values.description: Specifies the format for an application that was exported from LUIS.

values.name: Utf16CodeUnit
values.description:
The offset and length values will correspond to UTF-16 code units. Use this
option if your application is written in a language that support Unicode, for
example Java, JavaScript.

values.name: returnLongestOverlap
values.description:
When two or more components are found in the text and overlap, the component
with the longest set of characters is returned.

values.name: requireExactOverlap
values.description:
All components must overlap at the exact same characters in the text for the
entity to return. If one of the defined components is not matched or predicted,
the entity will not return.

values.name: separateComponents
values.description:
Every component's match or prediction is returned as a separate instance of the
entity.

values.name: combineComponents
values.description:
When two or more components are found in the text and overlap, the components'
spans are merged together into one span combining all of them.

values.name: advanced
values.description:
Trains using fine-tuned neural network transformer models. Can train
multilingual projects.

values.name: standard
values.description: Faster training times for quicker iterations.

values.name: percentage
values.description:
Split the data into training and test sets according to user-defined
percentages.

values.name: manual
values.description: Split the data according to the chosen dataset for every example in the data.

Clients.Name: ConversationsClient
Clients.Description: The language service API is a suite of natural language processing (NLP) skills built with best-in-class Microsoft machine learning algorithms. The API can be used to analyze unstructured text for tasks such as sentiment analysis, key phrase extraction, language detection and question answering. Further documentation can be found in https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cognitive-services/language-service/overview.The language service conversations API is a suite of natural language processing (NLP) skills that can be used to analyze structured conversations (textual or spoken). The synchronous API in this suite accepts a request and mediates among multiple language projects, such as LUIS Generally Available, Question Answering, Conversational Language Understanding, and then calls the best candidate service to handle the request. At last, it returns a response with the candidate service's response as a payload.\n\n In some cases, this API needs to forward requests and responses between the caller and an upstream service. The asynchronous APIs in this suite enable tasks like Conversation Summarization and Conversational PII detection.
